name: Morning Glory
description:
The artwork story :

A Birthday Tribute to Frida Kahlo,
Frida Kahlo was a Mexican
painter known for her many portraits, self-portraits,
and works inspired by the nature and artifacts of Mexico.
Inspired by the country's popular culture, she employed
a naïve folk art style to explore questions of identity,
postcolonialism, gender, class, and race in Mexican society
Born: July 6, 1907, Coyoacán, Mexico City, Mexico
Died: July 13, 1954, Coyoacán, Mexico City, Mexico

Made in: 2016
Frame: Acrylic + Oil on canvas
Size: 100x100cm
